'''Yamashina Clan''' (山科家) was a {{ill|Japanese court noble|ja|公家}} and later a {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族}} family. As a {{ill|Kuge|ja|公家}}, its rank was {{ill|Baronial House|ja|羽林家}}, and as a {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族}}, its title was that of a {{ill|Count|ja|伯爵}}.{{sfn|Odabe, Yūji|2006|p=326}}

== History ==
=== Feudal Period ===
The clan traces its origins to [[Fujiwara no Sanekuni]], the sixth son of [[Fujiwara no Ienaga|藤原家成]], a court noble from the late {{ill|Heian Period|ja|平安時代}}. The clan's name derives from its ancestral estates in [[Yamashina|山科]], Kyoto. Initially, it was known as the Reizei clan but later adopted the Yamashina name during the {{ill|Nanboku-chō period|ja|南北朝時代}} under {{ill|Yamashina Noriyuki|ja|山科教行}}.{{sfn|Hashimoto, Masanobu|2010|p=582}}

The Yamashina clan specialized in {{ill|Yūsoku kojitsu|ja|有職故実}}, particularly ceremonial attire and court music (especially {{ill|Shō|ja|笙}}).{{sfn|Hashimoto, Masanobu|2010|p=582}}

